54.9	Requiem_(Mozart)	Requiem (Mozart)	The Requiem Mass in D minor (K. 626) by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart was composed in Vienna in 1791 and left unfinished at the composer's death on December 5. A completion by Franz Xaver SÃ¼ssmayr was delivered to Count Franz von Walsegg, who had anonymously commissioned the piece for a requiem Mass to commemorate the February 14 anniversary of his wife's death.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9a/K626_Requiem_Mozart.jpg/220px-K626_Requiem_Mozart.jpg
